<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b> <span class="citation book">Godley, A. D. (ed.) (1920). <i>Herodotus, with an English translation</i>. Cambridge: Harvard UP.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Herodotus%2C+with+an+English+translation&amp;rft.aulast=Godley&amp;rft.aufirst=A.+D.+%28ed.%29&amp;rft.au=Godley%2C%26%2332%3BA.+D.+%28ed.%29&amp;rft.date=1920&amp;rft.place=Cambridge&amp;rft.pub=Harvard+UP&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Median_language"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <a href="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/cgi-bin/ptext?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.01.0126&amp;layout=&amp;loc=1.110" class="external text" rel="nofollow">(<i>Histories</i> 1.110)</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b> <span class="citation book">Hamilton, H. C. &amp; W. Falconer (1903). <i>The Geography of Strabo. Literally translated, with notes</i>. <b>3</b>. London: George Bell &amp; Sons.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Geography+of+Strabo.+Literally+translated%2C+with+notes&amp;rft.aulast=Hamilton&amp;rft.aufirst=H.+C.+%26+W.+Falconer&amp;rft.au=Hamilton%2C%26%2332%3BH.+C.+%26+W.+Falconer&amp;rft.date=1903&amp;rft.volume=3&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=George+Bell+%26+Sons&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Median_language"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> p. 125. <a href="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/cgi-bin/ptext?doc=Perseus:text:1999.01.0239:book=15:chapter=2:section=1" class="external text" rel="nofollow">(<i>Geography</i> 15.2)</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-Tafazzoli-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Tafazzoli_10-0">^</a></b> <span class="citation book" id="CITEREFTafazzoli1999">Tafazzoli, Ahmad (1999). <a href="http://www.iranica.com/newsite/articles/v9f2/v9f232.html" class="external text" rel="nofollow">"Fahlavīyāt"</a>. <i>Encyclopaedia Iranica</i>. <b>9.2</b>. New York: iranica.com<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.iranica.com/newsite/articles/v9f2/v9f232.html" class="external free" rel="nofollow">http://www.iranica.com/newsite/articles/v9f2/v9f232.html</a></span></span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Fahlav%C4%ABy%C4%81t&amp;rft.atitle=Encyclopaedia+Iranica&amp;rft.aulast=Tafazzoli&amp;rft.aufirst=Ahmad&amp;rft.au=Tafazzoli%2C%26%2332%3BAhmad&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.volume=9.2&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=iranica.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iranica.com%2Fnewsite%2Farticles%2Fv9f2%2Fv9f232.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Median_language"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span><sup class="noprint Inline-Template"><span title="&#160;since June 2010" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Link_rot" title="Wikipedia:Link rot">dead link</a></i>]</span></sup></li>
